# Page Title Style Rule - CRITICAL

## UPPERCASE PAGE TITLES RULE

**ALL main page titles (h1 headings) MUST be in UPPERCASE.**

### Rule Application

This rule applies to:
- ✅ Main page headings (h1 elements with large font sizes)
- ✅ Page titles displayed prominently at the top of pages
- ✅ Navigation/landing page titles
- ✅ Section titles for major content areas

### Examples of Correct Usage

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Uppercase main page title
<h1 className="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black text-white mb-2 tracking-wide">
  ALL ARTICLES
</h1>

// ✅ CORRECT - Uppercase column title
<h1 className="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black text-white mb-4 tracking-wide">
  BOOK CLUB
</h1>

// ✅ CORRECT - Uppercase submit page title
title: 'SUBMIT TO THE LOST ARCHIVES'
```

### What This Rule Does NOT Apply To

- ❌ Error messages (e.g., "Error", "Post Not Found")
- ❌ Loading states (e.g., "Loading...")
- ❌ Success messages (e.g., "✅ Authorization Code Received")
- ❌ Subheadings (h2, h3, etc.)
- ❌ Body text and descriptions
- ❌ Button labels
- ❌ Form labels

### Implementation Checklist

When creating or updating a page:

1. ✅ Check if the page has a main h1 heading
2. ✅ Verify the heading is in UPPERCASE
3. ✅ Ensure consistency with other page titles
4. ✅ Update meta tags (og:title, twitter:title) to match if needed

